prompt.user:
Project: {project_name} Client: {client_name} Methodology: {methodology} Service Lines: {service_lines}
Project Type Guidance: {project_type_guidance}
SOW Summary: {sow_summary}
Service Line Design Standards: {standards_context}
Platform Combination Patterns (proven integration patterns for this service line mix): {combinations_context}
Generated Requirements Context (if available): {requirements_context}
FORMAT GUIDE ONLY — READ CAREFULLY BEFORE GENERATING: The example below is for a COMPLETELY DIFFERENT fictional project (Meridian Insurance). DO NOT copy any of the following from the example into your output: - Endpoint paths (/claims, /policies, /meridian) — derive paths from THIS project's business domain - Entity names (Claim, Policy, Claimant) — use entities from THIS project's SOW and requirements - Numbers (100 req/min, 5000/hour) unless they appear in THIS project's context - Auth policy names (MeridianJWT, ClaimsServicePrincipal) — name these from THIS project The example shows ONLY the structure and depth of each API section. All content must come from the actual project context above.
FORMAT EXAMPLE (fictional project — structure only):
### [Service Line] APIs
#### [Feature Group — e.g., the actual feature from THIS project's requirements] | Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required | |--------|----------|-------------|---------------| | [HTTP method] | /[domain-entity]/[action] | [What this endpoint does in THIS project] | [Auth method from THIS project's stack] |
**Request Body** (key fields): ```json { "[field-from-this-project]": "[type] — [description tied to business operation]" } ```
**Response** (200 OK): ```json { "[field-from-this-project]": "[type] — [description]" } ```
**Error Responses**: [HTTP codes + when they occur in THIS project's context]
END OF FORMAT EXAMPLE.
Now generate the API design document for {project_name} — client {client_name}, service lines: {service_lines}. Every endpoint path, entity name, and field must come from the actual project context above. Do not copy names or numbers from the format example. Do NOT add a "Note:" section or any closing assumptions paragraph. Output ONLY markdown.
